# AWS & Bash 

## Objective

Learn how to use Bash to create and manage AWS services.

---

## What I Did

- Launched and terminated EC2 instances
- Created Security Groups and applied rules
- Built a basic VPC with public subnets and Internet Gateway
- Managed IAM users and groups
- Configured Route Tables
- Connected to the EC2 instance from a browser displaying a simple "Welcome" page

---

## Key Concepts

- Bash scripting for AWS CLI automation
- Network isolation and routing
- Security Groups and least privilege
- IAM fundamentals

---

## Result

Successfully automated the creation of AWS infrastructure and accessed a public EC2 instance using a web browser.
